description.narrative:
The development impact of the project is expected to include:

Increasing the electricity generation capacity from renewable sources by 100MW with about 220GWh generated annually;
Consequently, avoiding greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions of about 206,000 tCO2e annually helping to improve air quality and mitigate climate change;
Contributing to the economic development of one of the frontier provinces in China, by helping with the electrification of the province and neighboring provinces, procuring wind turbines from the local manufacturing facility, and contributing to foreign direct investment;
Supporting Chinas ambitious plan to increase renewable resources in the energy mix to generate 10% and 15% of its electricity from renewable sources by 2010 and 2020, respectively;
Helping to reduce reliance on finite coal resources for thermal power generation;
Promoting private sector participation in the wind power sector by supporting one of the few wind farms that are majority owned by private investors, thus sending a positive signal to domestic and international private investors and developers; and,
Contributing to job creation mainly during project design and construction with an estimated peak of about 200 local temporary workers.
